The paper discusses the integration of fields of science over time, which suggests a focus on interdisciplinary research. The paper also analyzes citation networks, indicating a focus on bibliometrics and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
